text: Emmanuel Kenmogne (born September 2, 1980) is a Belgian-Cameroonian professional footballer who last played as a striker for Persija Jakarta. He previously played for Malaysia Super League side, Kelantan FA. == Career == Kenmogne began his career with local club, Sablé FC, for whom he played in the CAF Champions League 2000. He next joined Africa Sports National of Côte d'Ivoire. Kenmogne moved to Belgium in 2002, where he played for R.A.A. Louviéroise and R.A.E.C. Mons in the Belgian First Division, before joining Royal Antwerp. ==Honours== ===Club=== Sable FC * Cameroon Première Division: 1999 * Super Coupe Roger Milla: 1999 R.A.A.
